rComments: The class is really interesting and he tries to make it as fun as possible.  Don't have to read the book as long as you take notes in class...though his lecture notes are sufficient.  His exams are kind of hard, even if you study a lot...it's all about application.  Great class and prof though.

Amazing class, and always interesting. I took this during the summer, and the only downside was the class's tendency to run five to fifteen minutes long, due to a lack of bells, but during fall and spring it shouldn't be a problem. As for difficulty, as long as you show up, you'll do fine.
